				<h2>What is CRM Automation?</h2>
				<p>CRM automation uses your customer relationship management system to automatically track, engage, and retain customers throughout their entire lifecycle. Instead of manually tracking customer health, sending follow-ups, or remembering to check in, your CRM handles it all automatically.</p>
				<p><strong>The result?</strong> You reduce customer churn, increase repeat buyers, achieve higher retention rates, and keep customers buying longer—all while saving countless hours of manual work.</p>

				<h2>Reduce Customer Churn with CRM Automation</h2>
				<p>Customer churn is a silent profit killer. Every customer who leaves takes not just their current value, but all their future purchases with them. CRM automation helps you reduce churn by identifying at-risk customers and intervening before they leave.</p>

				<h3>How CRM Automation Reduces Churn:</h3>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Automated health scores</strong> - Track engagement, usage, and satisfaction automatically</li>
					<li><strong>Early warning system</strong> - Get alerts when customers show signs of disengagement</li>
					<li><strong>Automatic interventions</strong> - Trigger re-engagement campaigns before it's too late</li>
					<li><strong>Win-back workflows</strong> - Automated sequences to reactivate churned customers</li>
					<li><strong>Feedback loops</strong> - Collect and act on customer feedback systematically</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Increase Repeat Buyers with Automated Workflows</h2>
				<p>The fastest path to revenue growth isn't acquiring more customers—it's getting existing customers to buy again. CRM automation makes it easy to increase repeat buyers through timely, personalized outreach.</p>

				<h3>CRM Workflows That Increase Repeat Buyers:</h3>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Repurchase triggers</strong> - Automated reminders based on purchase cycles</li>
					<li><strong>Personalized recommendations</strong> - Suggest products based on past behavior</li>
					<li><strong>Milestone offers</strong> - Special promotions at strategic intervals</li>
					<li><strong>Usage-based outreach</strong> - Reach out when customers might need more</li>
					<li><strong>Loyalty programs</strong> - Automated rewards for repeat purchases</li>
				</ul>

				<h2>Keep Customers Longer = Higher Retention Rates</h2>
				<p>Small improvements in retention create massive revenue impact. Acquiring a new customer costs 5-7x more than retaining an existing one. Higher retention rates mean predictable revenue and sustainable growth.</p>

